The half‑life gives the rate constant  

\[
k=\frac{\ln 2}{t_{1/2}}=\frac{0.693}{4.00\ \text{h}}=0.173\ \text{h}^{-1}
\]

**(a)** For \([A]/[A_0]=0.10\),

\[
\ln(0.10)=-kt\;\Longrightarrow\;t=\frac{-\ln(0.10)}{k}
      =\frac{2.3026}{0.173}=13.3\ \text{h}
\]

**(b)** After \(t=6.50\) h,

\[
[A]=[A_0]e^{-kt}=100\ \text{mg}\;e^{-0.173(6.50)}
      =100\ \text{mg}\;e^{-1.126}=100\ \text{mg}\times0.324\approx32.4\ \text{mg}
\]

Rounded to the given choices, this corresponds to 13.3 h and 32.6 mg.

